<div class="tldr-box">
  <h3>TL;DR, RazorpayX Payroll for Indian startups</h3>
  <p>The one-click payroll product from India's largest payment gateway. ~₹100/employee/month, salaries disbursed plus PF, ESI, PT, TDS handled in a single approval. Best for startups under 100 employees that want payroll done correctly without full HRMS overhead. Graduates well into Keka or greytHR as the team scales.</p>
  <a href="https://razorpay.com/payroll/" class="cta-button">Visit RazorpayX Payroll</a>
</div>

<p>For an Indian startup founder, payroll is the operational chore that combines highest stakes (people get angry if salary is wrong or late) with highest compliance risk (PF and TDS misses trigger notices). RazorpayX Payroll exists to compress this entire monthly cycle into a single approval click.</p>

<h2>What RazorpayX Payroll actually does</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Salary computation</strong>, CTC structuring, allowances, deductions, reimbursements, loans and advances.</li>
  <li><strong>Statutory deductions</strong>, PF (employee + employer), ESI (where applicable), Professional Tax (by state), TDS under Section 192, LWF.</li>
  <li><strong>Salary disbursement</strong>, Approved payroll triggers payments via Razorpay banking integration. Indian banks supported.</li>
  <li><strong>Statutory deposits</strong>, PF challan, ESI challan, TDS challan deposited via the platform.</li>
  <li><strong>Compliance filings</strong>, Monthly PF ECR, monthly ESI ECR, quarterly TDS return, annual Form 16, gratuity calc.</li>
  <li><strong>Employee self-service</strong>, Payslip download, IT declarations, leave application, reimbursement claims.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Where RazorpayX wins</h2>

<h3>One-click monthly close</h3>
<p>Approve payroll, salaries and statutory amounts disburse together. The "salary day" overhead for a small Indian startup goes from a day of back-and-forth to minutes.</p>

<h3>INR-native banking integration</h3>
<p>Razorpay's existing banking rails (RazorpayX) move money. No separate bank file uploads, no missed UPI, no manual NEFT entries.</p>

<h3>Compliance correctness</h3>
<p>PF, ESI, PT, TDS handled automatically. The kind of corrections that take a CA two days to clean up after a sloppy month are simply not allowed to happen.</p>

<h3>Indian payment native, GST invoice automatic</h3>
<p>Subscription billed in INR with UPI / Indian cards, GST invoice with input credit, tax deductible.</p>

<h2>Best Indian use cases</h2>

<h3>Early-stage Indian startups (5-50 employees)</h3>
<p>The clearest fit. Founder + 1 ops person can run payroll end-to-end with minimal CA dependency. Statutory compliance handled correctly from month 1.</p>

<h3>Indian consulting firms and agencies</h3>
<p>10-30 employees, mostly consultant cost structure, reimbursement-heavy expense patterns. RazorpayX handles this clean.</p>

<h3>Companies in transition to formalised HR</h3>
<p>Before hiring a dedicated HRBP, RazorpayX is the bridge that lets founders run payroll properly. Migrating to Keka or greytHR is straightforward when you outgrow.</p>

<h2>Where RazorpayX is not the right tool</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>You need OKR, performance management, hiring workflow</strong>, Use Keka. RazorpayX is payroll-only.</li>
  <li><strong>Heavy attendance/biometric workflows</strong>, greytHR has deeper attendance modules.</li>
  <li><strong>200+ employees with multi-state, multi-entity ops</strong>, Mid-market HRMS is more flexible.</li>
  <li><strong>Global payroll (US, EU employees)</strong>, Use Rippling or Deel.</li>
</ul>

